Since you can hack it together super quickly without difficult design choices.\n15 regs (+ zero register)\n64 instruction ROM size\n8 data bit-width\nAnd for instruction width, I went with `reg+reg+reg+opcode+condition+imm/jump` which is `4+4+4+3+3+6 = 24`, 24 bits being a nice round number.\nFor opcodes, I am only using two add/sub, so the remaining are free to choose.
